<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1438,151,932]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
Among the material available this is the most size-variable species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolton &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2012" box="[1030,1094,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silens">
<emphasis box="[1030,1094,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">silens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex; see notes under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolton &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2012" box="[1394,1428,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rex">
<emphasis box="[1394,1428,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">rex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its closest relative appears to be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolton &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2012" box="[512,552,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dux">
<emphasis box="[512,552,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">dux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differences are noted there. Gary Alpert (MCZC) has observed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolton &amp; Fisher" authorityYear="2012" box="[1271,1377,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sicaria">
<emphasis box="[1271,1377,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">S. sicaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
raiding an arboreal nest of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Emery" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[408,618,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Terataner" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alluaudi">
<emphasis box="[408,618,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Terataner alluaudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the entire raid took less than 20 minutes. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1891" box="[1145,1255,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1145,1255,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Simopone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
workers moved rapidly among lower tree branches until they reached the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1912" box="[811,920,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Terataner" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[811,920,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Terataner</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nest in a twig, about 50 yards distant, which they entered. They emerged carrying the victim’s brood; captured adult 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1912" box="[969,1078,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Terataner" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[969,1078,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Terataner</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discarded and dropped to the ground.
</paragraph>
